H.B. 969
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Apr 10, 2025
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH10436-NB-125
Short Title: Study the Abolition of Contrib. Negligence. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Longest.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO DIRECT THE LEGISLATIVE RESEARCH COMMISSION TO STUDY THE
3 ABOLITION OF CONTRIBUTORY NEGLIGENCE.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. The Legislative Research Commission (LRC) shall study the abolition
6 of contributory negligence in this State. As part of the study, the LRC shall do all of the following:
7 (1) Determine whether the abolition of contributory negligence would improve
8 measure outcomes for the citizens of this State.
9 (2) Determine whether maintaining contributory negligence is harming citizens,
10 and in what primary ways.
11 (3) Evaluate the fiscal impacts of the adoption of a new negligence framework,
12 including costs to individuals, consumers, businesses, insurance, and other
13 appropriate areas.
14 (4) Make a recommendation as to what negligence framework would be most
15 beneficial to the State, including modified and pure comparative negligence.
16 SECTION 2. The LRC shall submit a report on its study, including any legislative
17 recommendations, to the 2026 Regular Session of the 2025 General Assembly upon its
18 convening.
19 SECTION 3. This act is effective when it becomes law.
*DRH10436-NB-125*

